# Módulos HCL — Convenciones

Cuando trabajes en archivos dentro de `modules/`, consulta el skill `xancloud-iac-modules` en `.cursor/skills/` para las convenciones completas.

## Quick reference

### Estructura obligatoria por módulo
```
modules/{category}/{name}/
├── main.tf
├── variables.tf
├── outputs.tf
├── versions.tf
├── locals.tf
├── README.md          # Auto-generado (terraform-docs)
├── examples/simple/
└── tests/basic.tftest.hcl
```

### versions.tf siempre:
```hcl
terraform {
  required_version = ">= 1.11.0"
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 5.0"
    }
  }
}
```

### Tags en locals.tf:
```hcl
locals {
  common_tags = {
    Environment = var.environment
    Project     = var.project
    Owner       = var.owner
    ManagedBy   = "opentofu"
    CostCenter  = var.cost_center
  }
  name_prefix = "${var.project}-${var.environment}"
}
```

### Variables comunes (siempre presentes):
- `environment` (string, validation: dev/staging/prod)
- `project` (string, validation: lowercase alphanumeric + hyphens)
- `owner` (string)
- `cost_center` (string)
- `extra_tags` (map(string), default: {})

### Sin backend block en módulos. Sin DynamoDB. Sin Terraform Cloud.
